### 🟡 Functional & Architectural Concerns

| Issue | Why it matters | Fix |
|-------|----------------|-----|
| Hardcoded config values | Makes environment-specific tuning impossible | Use `process.env` for origins, limits, and credentials |
| No graceful `413` handling | Clients get generic errors when exceeding limits | Add a global error handler to return structured `413 Payload Too Large` responses |
| Global permissive middleware | Increases attack surface | Apply restrictive defaults globally, relax per-route only when necessary |

